Alliance Data Systems Corp Announces Agreements With eBay Inc's PayPal
Tuesday, 6 Aug 2013 07:30am EDT
Alliance Data Systems Corp announced that its Retail Services business, which manages more than 120 branded credit programs, has come to multiple agreements with payments industry PayPal, an eBay Inc subsidiary. Under a multi-year agreement with PayPal, Alliance Data will become an issuer for Bill Me Later credit products and will maintain a partial interest in the receivables generated under the program. Bill Me Later is a PayPal service that lets you buy now and pay later once you're approved and is a secure, instant, and reusable credit line that doesn't require qualifying customers to keep another credit card in their wallets. Bill Me Later is offered as a payment option at thousands of online stores.Â 
